{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01DBnqiD6NCwUwzdsL6iNqWE","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The node crdb-cluster-2 (secure mode) can't contact the other nodes (crdb-cluster-0 and crdb-cluster-1) because they're still running in insecure mode. The TLS handshake will fail between a secure node and insecure nodes.\n\nI have a few options:\n1. Force restart all pods at once (scale down to 0, then up to 3) - this will cause downtime but the cluster will come up in secure mode\n2. Wait for the rolling update (but it's blocked because crdb-cluster-2 isn't ready)\nThe rolling update is stuck because crdb-cluster-2 can't communicate with the insecure nodes, so it won't become ready. The best approach is to scale the StatefulSet down to zero and back up to three, which will restart everything simultaneously and let the cluster transition to secure mode all at once, though it'll cause a brief outage.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":832,"cache_read_input_tokens":37729,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":832},"output_tokens":33,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"9a076bb7-1b74-4528-844e-9dce686c56b1","uuid":"206a34b8-ed97-4e06-8323-7424bfb0cabf","request_id":"req_011Ccc9WbdgDgqTusQ1EQM8g"}
